*Code*
{code}
class Fatal {
  object o
  import o.foo._

  implicit def i(tree: Object) = new Object
}
{code}

The import on the third line obviously fails, but if it is followed by an implicit method definition, this causes a fatal error when executing scalac. The version of scalac used is _Scala compiler version 2.6.1.13465.20071206-172552 -- (c) 2002-2007 LAMP/EPFL_.

*What happened*

When compiling with scalac, this code results in 
{code}
$$ scalac src/Fatal.scala
src/Fatal.scala:5: error: illegal cyclic reference involving value <import>
        implicit def i(tree: Object) = new Object
                                           ^
error: fatal error: symbol value <import> has bad type: <error>
{code}
When compiling with ant, this code results in
{code}
